result.execSummary:
The defendant Markae R Kimble-Holmes was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: with Elements of criminal offenses to which plea is being entered.

10:40 AM; Case called for Hearing.  Defendant Markae R Kimble-Holmes in court, in custody at WCJ, with attorney Eryn M Menden.   Patrick Ryan Campbell appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court notes a plea questionnaire has been filed and inquires how the matter is proceeding.  Atty. Menden confirms her client is prepared to proceed with plea and sentencing today.  State recites the offer.  Atty. Menden confirms the offer.  Court conducts plea colloquy with the defendant.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1, Court finds defendant guilty.

Sentencing arguments made by the State.
Sentencing arguments made by Atty. Menden.
Defendant presents statements.

COUNT 1:
The Court Orders the Following:

30 Days Jail Straigh Time (Credit - 37 days) - TIME SERVED.

FINE or COSTS: Waived by the Court.
	
DNA Surcharge: $200.00;

DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 
 
Total costs/fine/forfeiture: Court to apply the remaining 7 Days Credit, $350.00, PAID IN FULL.
